# =================================================================
# Common .dockerignore — applied to ANY `docker build` from repo root
# whose Dockerfile does NOT have a sibling `<Dockerfile>.dockerignore`.
# Image-specific exclusions live in `<Dockerfile>.dockerignore` (e.g.
# Dockerfile.explore.dockerignore) so each image's build context is
# right-sized without breaking the others.
# =================================================================

# Credentials — MUST NOT enter any build context. Belt-and-suspenders
# defence: even if a Dockerfile uses `COPY . .` these never leak.
**/*-key.json
**/service-account*.json
**/service_account*.json
**/firebase-adminsdk-*.json
**/credentials.json
**/*-credentials.json
**/.env
**/.env.*

# Build artefacts and ephemeral state.
**/.venv/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.cache/
**/*.bak
*.bak
**/coverage/
.coverage

# Editor / IDE / VCS metadata.
.git/
.gitignore
.idea/
.vscode/
.DS_Store

# Per-package PLAN.md (gitignored anyway; defensive).
**/PLAN.md
